2023's  driving word: BOUNDARIES 🌿❤🌟

A personal boundary is the practice of openly communicating and asserting personal values as way to preserve and protect against having them compromised or violated. 

I have a love/hate relationship with boundaries to be honest. I respect other people's boundaries, yet sometimes I let mine be compromised. I unfortunately will go along, to get along.. So.  I NEED boundaries so I can make sure I'm not setting myself up for disappointment expecting people to be ME. How I love and move throughout this world is beautiful, I will have personal boundaries so that takers won't overtake. I can love, be kind, be empathetic and still have limits on it 🙏🏾 

So it can be in my FB memories in perpetuity..

Running list of driving words: 

2016: NO- Stop overextending myself. Stop being guilted in loyalty. Saying no to others and YES to me and started to focus more on what made me happy.

2017: Freedom -Free to be the woman I want to be. Free from people's opinions of me.I wore what I wanted.. Said what I wanted and how I wanted to say it.

2018: Empower- Live out loud. Show other women that they could as well... because it's dope to be who you are UNAPOLOGETICALLY.. ❤️

2019:  Affirm. I affirmed to honor my natural gifts and walk in my purpose

2020: Align.. I wanted to align my chakras and to make crooked paths straight..

2021: Reciprocity- To not leave myself drained by takers. To be poured into the way I pour. 

2022: Alchemy- to know that good things can flow to me. That I can create my own magic ✨️

2023: BOUNDARIES x STANDARDS 

#Boundaries #Standards

1. Continue to meal prep BUT prep more healthy snacks. I eat well, then snack.. So I need to prepare for when I get cravings 🍪

2. Add back in more outdoor cardio. It proves time and again that it's essential to my total wellness 

3. Cut back on that brown liquor 🫣 Bourbon/Whiskey on the rocks with a slice of orange 🥃🍊 is my favorite.. But reduce it to only on the weekends and even then only a glass or 2

Health is wealth. Secure the bag 💰

Community fridge update. Tough lessons learned. When human nature is involved, no system can be perfect. 🫶🏾

I didn't post in April because I was so busy.. but please believe that I was still being of service 😊🫶🏾

So, I found out every Sunday after I filled the fridge, that one individual was getting most of the food.. but the thing is.. Food insecurity is real.

If you don't know where your next meal will come from, I understand the mindset of securing more food for yourself. Can't call a possibly starving person selfish. 

But.. what I do now..

I make multiple grocery drop offs during the week. I have learned NOT to put the whole grocery haul in there at once 🙈

I also learned that as much as I LOVE cooking for the community, it takes a lot of time and can be exhausting. So, doing grocery drop offs is not letting anyone down, but more so keeping myself from being too overwhelmed.

But, if I plan to cook...I prefer to take it directly to the community either to our unhoused (homeless) or to the Senior Citizen housing. 

To be of service is a blessing, but also be mindful of your mental and physical health while doing so. And still..WE light up the dark ✨️ ✨️✨️✨️✨️

Walking treadmill pad thorough review:

Overall: I LOVE IT! 🥳

Personal preference: I did find that for me, walking at around 2.6 speed was a brisk enough walk to be able to have a more enjoyable experience. In the morning,  I've decided I rather go for enjoyable. ☀️😊

Other pros and cons.. 

😣Cons:

•It's not as quiet as it claims

•Cord was too short. Had to go purchase an appliance/heavy duty extension cord for it about $17

•Does not fit under the couch as they claimed

•Shipping arrived about 5 days later than expected delivery date

•If you’re not careful or going too fast you'll hit the rear bumber gaurds. When I'm going faster speeds, I position it in front of a mirror to help with balance and focus.

🥳Pros:

•It works as expected even on higher speeds

•Without the traditional treadmill handles its less bulky and easier to maneuver 

•On the days it was storming outside,  I was still able to get a walk accomplished

A recap of 2023's driving word : BOUNDARIES x STANDARDS 

What I wrote and my expectations of 2023 👇🏾~~~~~~~~~~~~
A personal boundary is the practice of openly communicating and asserting personal values as way to preserve and protect against having them compromised or violated. 

I have a love/hate relationship with boundaries to be honest. I respect other people's boundaries, yet sometimes I let mine be compromised. I unfortunately will go along, to get along.. So.  I NEED boundaries so I can make sure I'm not setting myself up for disappointment expecting people to be ME. How I love and move throughout this world is beautiful, I will have personal boundaries so that takers won't overtake. I can love, be kind, be empathetic and still have limits on it 🙏🏾 

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

‼️👉🏾 What happened and what I learned in 2023:
Mannnn. When you set firm boundaries and stick with them, be prepared to lose people. Then prepare yourself to have to grieve the loss of a person who is still living. It's painful. It's painful to see people aren't willing to treat you how you want to be treated. To show effort and make you a priority. I had to learn to navigate projection. It wasn't about their behavior but more about what I can accept for myself to move forward in healthy ways. I will not negotiate how I am to be treated. What I found overall,  is that once I communicate how I feel and my expectations, if someone is unwilling to meet them.. KEEP IT MOVING. I believe in communication, what I refuse to do is allow anyone in my life to treat me less than.  I respectfully remove myself from people and situations that are harmful to my mental, emotional and spiritual health. Do you, how you do. Just without me ✌🏾

2024's driving word next post. 🫶🏾

2024's driving word: INTENTIONAL 

"Being intentional means making deliberate choices to reflect what is most important to us. Becoming intentional can help us maintain a positive mindset, reach goals, experience more clarity, and be more present." 

"Get busy living or get busy dying" -Redd 

I spent my 20's and 30's acquiring material things that I couldn't afford in my childhood. Desperately clawing my way out of a poverty mindset and generational poverty trauma. 

In 2024, it is my INTENTION to have more experiences vs. acquiring more things. More travel, more classes for things I want to learn or enjoy such as pottery, cooking, baking, etc. More life and life abundantly. Removing the fear that when I express more, I get less. That's trauma. I can have an INTENTIONAL life of joy without fear of loss.. That is the heart and soul work that I must do. Thank God for therapy ✨️✨️✨️ I promise myself, I will open my heart to the possibility of more 🤲🏾🫶🏾❤️ 🙏🏾

Intentional 🤲🏾🥰 ❤️✨️✨️
